Todo List Full Stack Application

This is a Todo List application developed using Django and React. It allows users to manage their tasks with features for creating, updating, completing, and deleting tasks.


Technologies Used

Backend: Django REST Framework
Frontend: React
Database: SQLite (Django's default for development)
Api Testing: Postman


Features

Create Task: Users can add new tasks with a title, description, and due date.
Update Task: Tasks can be edited to change the title, description, completion status, or due date.
Complete Task: Tasks can be marked as completed, which strikes through the task title.
Delete Task: Users can remove tasks they no longer need.
Pagination: Tasks are paginated on the frontend to improve loading times and user experience.


Backend Setup

Install Dependencies: Navigate to the backend directory and install Python dependencies:
pip install -r requirements.txt

Run Migrations: Apply database migrations to create the necessary tables:
python manage.py migrate

Run Server: Start the Django development server:
python manage.py runserver

The backend server will run at http://localhost:8000/admin


Frontend Setup

Install Dependencies: Navigate to the frontend directory and install npm dependencies:
npm install

Run Development Server: Start the React development server:
npm start
The frontend development server will run at http://localhost:3000.

Build Production: To build the production-ready frontend files:
npm run build


API Endpoints
GET /api/todos/: Retrieve paginated list of all todos.
POST /api/todos/: Create a new todo.
GET /api/todos/
/: Retrieve details of a specific todo.
PUT /api/todos/
/: Update details of a specific todo.
DELETE /api/todos/
/: Delete a specific todo.


